name: cyclic-guanylate-specific phosphodiesterase
comment: Requires Mg2+ or Mn2+ for activity and is inhibited by Ca2+ and Zn2+. Contains a heme unit. This enzyme linearizes cyclic di-3,5-guanylate, the product of EC 2.7.7.65, diguanylate cyclase and an allosteric activator of EC 2.4.1.12, cellulose synthase (UDP-forming), rendering it inactive [1]. It is the balance between these two enzymes that determines the cellular level of c-di-GMP [1].
